      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'implement the spectral feature extraction step' as if it were a distinct pipeline module, but the paper describes Chemprop-IR as an end-to-end architecture where molecular encoding (via MPNN) and phase metadata concatenation are integrated, not separated into a standalone feature extraction step.",
        "The card's expected outputs suggest extracting features from test molecules (spectral features tensor), but the paper's actual pipeline takes SMILES strings as input and outputs predicted absorbance vectors. There is no intermediate spectral feature extraction from test data.",
        "The research question asks about 'spectral features that chemprop-IR implements to extend chemprop,' which could be interpreted as asking what new features are added. The paper identifies phase information (one-hot encoded) as the key extension, but this is metadata concatenation, not spectral feature extraction in the sense the card implies."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:10:58.919926+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
