      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our method builds upon the Chemprop architecture developed by Yang et al. Chemprop consists of a directed MPNN and a feedforward neural network (FFNN) readout... Chemprop-IR uses an extension of the Chemprop network structure that specializes in the prediction of IR spectra, in the form of 1801 output elements.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper clearly demonstrates that extending a general-purpose MPNN (Chemprop) with specialized output layers and feature integration is necessary for IR spectral prediction tasks.",
