    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neural-network-architecture-extension/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The molecular vector following this concatenation is size 2205 for experimental spectra models and 2200 for computed spectra models. After phase feature concatenation, the resulting vector is fed to a FFNN for readout of the model results. For each intermediate layer in the FFNN, the produced vector size is 2200. The fi nal layer of the FFNN provides an output size of 1801.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly validates parameter flow and output shapes at each stage of the extended architecture, demonstrating the expected output behavior.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
