      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our method builds upon the Chemprop architecture developed by Yang et al. Chemprop consists of a directed MPNN and a feedforward neural network (FFNN) readout... Chemprop-IR uses an extension of the Chemprop network structure that specializes in the prediction of IR spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Chemprop is the base architecture and Chemprop-IR extends it. However, the 'spectral features' are not described as a separate module added to Chemprop; rather, Chemprop-IR is an extension that specializes the entire architecture for spectral prediction (1801 output elements for absorbance values, phase feature concatenation, SID loss function). The extension is architectural, not modular.",
