      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemprop-IR uses an extension of the Chemprop network structure that specializes in the prediction of IR spectra... The initial input to the model is a SMILES string, which is interpreted as a 2D molecular graph.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes Chemprop-IR as an extension of Chemprop for spectral prediction and validates forward passes with SMILES inputs. However, the paper does not describe a workflow of 'implementing a new module' and then 'verifying instantiation'\u2014it presents Chemprop-IR as a complete, published software package. The validation described in the paper is post-hoc performance evaluation on test sets, not pre-training validation of newly added modules.",
