      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SMILES input format and output dimensionality (1801 absorbance values). However, the paper does not describe a pre-training validation workflow. Instead, it describes the complete training pipeline with pretraining on computed spectra and refinement on experimental spectra. The paper does not present a use case of 'verifying compilation before training'\u2014it assumes the model is already built and proceeds directly to training.",
