      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemprop-IR uses an extension of the Chemprop network structure that specializes in the prediction of IR spectra... The phase of the molecule is introduced to the molecular fingerprint vector following message passing.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes chemprop-IR as a specialized architecture with domain-specific features (e.g., phase information) for IR prediction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-feature-engineering",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when working with the chemprop-IR architecture, which requires spectral features designed for IR spectral prediction",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:19.556146+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In Chemprop-IR, molecules are encoded using a directed message passing neural network, allowing for molecule latent representations to be learned and optimized for the task of spectral predictions... The structure of Chemprop-IR first encodes molecules with a MPNN before further processing the output in a FFNN.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes exactly this architecture: chemprop (MPNN base) extended with additional layers (FFNN readout) for spectral prediction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Integrate a spectral features module as an extension layer into the chemprop base message passing neural network architecture to enable infrared spectral predictions on molecular graphs.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The directed MPNN constructs a learned vector representation, or molecular fingerprint, from a given molecular graph by message passing... The molecular vector following this concatenation is fed to a FFNN for readout of the model results... The final layer of the FFNN provides an output size of 1801.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates composition of MPNN (molecular graph encoder) with FFNN (spectral feature transformer) to produce 1801-element spectral output vectors.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill bridges molecular graph representations with spectral property outputs by composing the base MPNN with learned spectral feature transformations.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our method builds upon the Chemprop architecture developed by Yang et al. Chemprop consists of a directed MPNN and a feedforward neural network (FFNN) readout.",
      "asbval:note": "Chemprop is confirmed as the base MPNN architecture. The paper cites Yang et al. 2019 as the original Chemprop work.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "chemprop: Base message passing neural network architecture that processes molecular graphs and produces learned molecular representations; the foundation to which the spectral features module is attached.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemprop-IR has been developed as a software package for the prediction of IR spectra through the use of machine learning... Chemprop-IR uses an extension of the Chemprop network structure that specializes in the prediction of IR spectra, in the form of 1801 output elements.",
      "asbval:note": "Chemprop-IR is explicitly described as an extension of Chemprop for IR spectral prediction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "chemprop-IR: Extended architecture combining chemprop base MPNN with spectral features module for infrared spectral predictions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Model training incorporates spectra metrics and normalization techniques that offer better performance with spectral predictions than standard practice in regression models... The model makes use of pretraining using quantum chemistry calculations and ensembling of multiple submodels to improve generalizability and performance.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates extending chemprop to predict spectral properties (1801-element vectors) rather than scalar properties, with specialized training techniques.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have a trained or untrained chemprop base model (graph convolution + readout layers) and need to extend it to predict infrared spectral properties rather than scalar molecular properties.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The initial input to the model is a SMILES string, which is interpreted as a 2D molecular graph... The prediction model is an ensemble of 10 individually trained submodels. Spectra are represented as vectors with 1801 normalized absorbances (one every 2 cm\u22121 from 400 to 4000 cm\u22121).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SMILES input and spectral vector targets (1801 absorbance values).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "The trigger is the availability of a molecular graph representation (SMILES or explicit graph) paired with target infrared spectral data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-features-module-integration/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MPNN weights from the initial model were carried over to the final model training and frozen, holding constant the encoding model learned in the initial model... Each of the 10 final submodels were initialized with different FFNN weights.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates transfer learning where MPNN weights (molecular representation encoder) are frozen and reused, while FFNN weights (spectral feature extractor) are trained separately.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_jcim_1c00055",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-features-module-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "The goal is to reuse the learned molecular representations from chemprop while adding spectral-specific feature extraction.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:13:31.744067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
